<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Suggesting an anti-random pkilling enforcement squad</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Unicron">Unicron</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:15 p.m. 1/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Suggesting an anti-random pkilling enforcement squad<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Ok, damn, i think i have read just about every one of these posts and thought about every side to the issue and i think one of the best ways to take care of this (since the develepors aren't) is an enforcement squad, kinda of like a volunteer firefighter, except volunteer cops.

<P>I am just thinking of a squad, town based, that is available to take care of the random pkillers that hunt down newbies and the like. Maybe the squad has a backup character (ranger, for example) that specifically deals with these cases. We take a complaint, such as someone got mowed down while picking flowers by 5 Kewldoodz, and decide a course of action. This team would have to be pretty strong to deal with a large group. There could be wanted posters set up on the message boards so when someone spots a character that is wanted, the squad can regulate. I am pretty much just thinking outloud here, so i am not sure of the logistics. I think this could be a good idea, and ensure a sense of community and justice and promote good Roleplaying.
<P>Please feel free to email me at unicron@mindless.com or reply on here. I would love to be a part of this and get it goin.
<P>+PvP forever...
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
